  • Time: 7:00pm - 7:40pm

  • Zoom meeting

    • Each student will be assigned to a Zoom meeting group.

    • The allocation of the Zoom meeting groups will be announced on LumiNUS before March 8

    • You must join only the assigned Zoom meeting on the test day.

  • Scope of test: Lectures 3, 5, & 6 (SQL parts 1-3)

  • Closed book test (with one double-sided A4-sized cheatsheet)

1. Hardware & Software Setup

You will need to use two devices (PC & mobile phone) for the mock midterm test with the following software.

  • Software to be installed on PC

    • Examplify for taking the online test.

    • Panopto for recording your PC screen during the test.

    • PostgreSQL for detecting syntax errors in your SQL answers.

  • Software to be installed on phone

    • Zoom (Android, iOS) for online proctoring.

You must install all the required software and check that they are working before the mock midterm test.

You should have already installed both Examplify (version 2.8) and PostgreSQL (version 14.1 or 14.2) by now.

You will be using Panopto (via LumiNUS-based interface) to record your PC screen. If you are new to this software, refer to Installing & Using Panopto on how to install and use Panopto.

The mock midterm test will be using Examplify in Non-secure block Internet mode. This mode performs a partial lockdown of your PC: you will not be able to connect to the Internet, but you can run other programs and switch between windows. Unlike your Examplify assignments, you will not to able to suspend your Examplify test.

  • Using Examplify on your PC

    • Ensure that your PC meets the requirements to use Examplify.

    • Ensure that you are using Examplify version 2.8. If not, upgrade your Examplify following these instructions.

    • Wireless accessories (e.g. wireless mouse and keyboards) are not recommended because Examplify may block wireless communications or it can be affected by interference from other devices. Should you require the use of such accessories, you are advised to obtain the wired equivalent.

    • There must be at least 4GB available space on your PC’s disk storage.

  • Using Zoom on your phone

    • Ensure that your phone meets the requirements to be used for Zoom proctoring.

    • Ensure that you’re using the latest version of Zoom. You can upgrade to the latest version following these instructions.

    • You should keep your phone cabled to the charger during the duration of your test because the Zoom app can consume significant battery power.

    • Test your zoom installation using NUS Zoom Test Site to ensure that you can sign in to a Zoom session comfortably and that your name is displayed correctly.

      • NUS Zoom test site’s meeting ID: 947 0512 6907

      • NUS Zoom test site’s passcode: ZSN52x

2. Zoom Proctoring Protocol

  • The mock test will be proctored using Zoom running on your phone.

  • The Zoom video feed from your phone camera will be recorded by the proctor.

  • Your phone camera must be positioned to capture one side of your face, both hands with table & the entire PC screen as illustrated above. You may use a phone stand to help with the positioning of your phone.

  • Your phone should be oriented in landscape mode and be connected to the charger. To prevent your Zoom video feed from being disconnected, you should disable the sleep/screen off mode on your phone. You should not use privacy screen protector on your phone.

  • You are to record your PC screen using Panopto before you unlock your Examplify test paper.

    • Refer to Installing & Using Panopto for details on how to record your PC screen and upload your recording.

  • You are allowed to use only a single screen. If you’re using an external monitor, the laptop screen must be switched off.

3. Preparations Before Test Day

  • The Examplify test paper will be available for download on March 7 from 12pm onwards

    • Start Examplify on your PC to download the test paper by March 7

    • You can download the test paper only once.

    • It is important that you download the test paper on the device to be used for taking the test.

    • You must download the test paper by March 7.

  • You must rename your Zoom display name to be the same as the name on your student card. This renaming must be completed before you join your assigned Zoom meeting on the test day.

    • To change your display name on your phone, click the Settings icon at the bottom, click your profile information on top, and click "Display Name" to edit the text box named "DISPLAY NAME". Note that you will not be allowed to enter the test’s Zoom meeting if your display name is not appropriately renamed.

  • Test your phone’s Zoom installation using NUS Zoom Test Site to ensure that you can sign in to a Zoom session comfortably and that your name is displayed correctly. Practise positioning your phone camera to capture one side of your face, both hands with table & the entire PC screen as illustrated in Zoom Proctoring Protocol.

    • Zoom test site’s meeting ID: 947 0512 6907

    • Zoom test site’s passcode: ZSN52x

  • Practise using Panopto to record your PC screen following the steps in Using Panopto.

  • If you’re using Windows OS on your PC,

    • Disable Windows Update before your test and enable it back after the test.

    • Disable Anti-virus software before your test and enable it back after the test.

  • Ensure that the things that you need for the test are within easy reach on your desk on the test day. Only the following additional items are allowed on your desk:

    • Student card (or passport if you don’t have your student card), pen/pencil, eraser

    • One A4-sized sheet of scratch paper

    • One A4-sized, double-sided cheat sheet (handwritten and/or printed)

    • Water bottle or cup/can of beverage

4. Exam Rules

  1. You must comply with all the instructions from the proctor.

  2. You are not allowed to communicate with anyone (whether in person or online) except with the proctor, examiner, or CIT personnel for assistance.

  3. You are not allowed to have any other electronic devices (including mobile phone, tablet, notebook, smart watch, electronic dictionary, secondary computer monitor, etc.) within reach or sight or hearing from where you are sitting for the test with the exceptions of the test device (PC/laptop) and the phone used for remote proctoring.

  4. You are not allowed to use headphone/earphone during the test.

  5. Your Zoom video feed & PC’s screen recording must be turned on throughout the test.

  6. You are not allowed to move away from your Zoom video feed (except during authorized breaks) throughout the entire test.

  7. If you are a late comer (i.e., you joined the Zoom meeting after the announcement of the test paper password), you must submit your test paper immediately after the proctor has announced stop writing.

  8. You are not allowed to use your PC or phone after submitting your test answers, and you must remain seated until the end of the test.

  9. You are not allowed to leave the Zoom meeting until you are told to do so by the proctor.

  10. Any student who is found to have contravened any of the above rules will be liable for disciplinary action that may result in his/her expulsion from the University.

5. Test Day

5.1. Downloading of Database Schema

  • The database schema used in the mock test will be released two hours before the test.

  • You can download the database schema file schema.sql from LumiNUS > Files > Mock Midterm from 5pm onwards

    • It is important that you download this file before you unlock the Examplify test paper

  • You may use the schema file on PostgreSQL to check the syntax of your SQL queries.

5.2. Admission into Zoom Meeting

  • Join your assigned Zoom meeting at 7pm.

    • Start the Zoom app on your phone.

    • Login using Sign in with SSO with company domain as nus-sg and your NUSNET ID.

    • DO NOT input your NUSNET ID and password into the default username and password field. Sign in using SSO.

  • The proctor will admit you from Zoom’s waiting room after verifying your display name.

    • If the proctor calls your name, please show your student card to your phone camera for additional identity verification.

  • Ensure that your Zoom settings are configured correctly:

    • Mute your Zoom mic (bottom left mic icon).

    • Turn on your Zoom speaker (top left speaker icon) and adjust the audio volume of your phone to ensure that you can hear announcements from the proctor.

    • Start Zoom video (bottom left video camera icon).

    • You must not use any virtual background for the Zoom meeting.

  • Adjust your phone camera as necessary to capture one side of your face, both hands with table & the entire PC screen as illustrated in Zoom Proctoring Protocol.

    • Your phone should be oriented in landscape mode and be connected to the charger. To prevent your Zoom video feed from being disconnected, you should disable the sleep/screen off mode on your phone. You should not use privacy screen protector on your phone.

  • The proctor may request you to adjust your phone camera if it is not suitably positioned.

5.3. Recording of PC Screen

  • Login to LumiNUS to start the recording of your PC screen using Panopto by following steps 1 to 11 in Using Panopto.

  • It is important that you start the screen recording before you unlock the Examplify test paper. Once you’ve unlocked the test paper and start the test, Internet access will be blocked and you will not be able to start Panopto from LumiNUS.

  • Start the Examplify application.

5.4. Start of Test

  • The proctor will announce the test paper password by sharing his/her Zoom screen to show the password and also reading out the password.

  • Enter the password to unlock your Examplify test paper

  • You may start answering the test questions once you have unlocked the test paper.

5.5. During the Test

  • Announcements

    • Any announcement by the proctor will be made via Zoom audio. The proctor may also use Zoom’s share screen to display the announcement.

    • It is important to ensure that your phone’s Zoom audio has been adjusted sufficiently loud for you to hear the proctor’s announcements. You should also periodically check your phone’s screen for any announcement via Zoom’s share screen (in case you missed the audio announcement).

  • Seeking clarifications on test questions

    • You are allowed to ask only boolean questions (i.e., questions that have a yes or no answer) during the test.

    • To ask a question, use Zoom chat on your phone as follows:

      • Tap on the phone to show a menu at the bottom of the Zoom app.

      • Tap on the More button ("…​") at the right corner of the menu to show a submenu and click on the Raise Hand button.

      • When the proctor has cleared your raised hand icon, use Zoom chat to type your question.

      • The proctor will forward your question to the examiner. The proctor will reply with one of three possible replies (yes, no, or na). A na reply means that your question is not appropriate and it is not answered.

  • Taking a bathroom break

    • To request permission to take a bathroom break, use the following procedure:

      • Tap on the phone to show a menu at the bottom of the Zoom app.

      • Tap on the More button ("…​") at the right corner of the menu to show a submenu and click on the Raise Hand button.

      • When the proctor has cleared your raised hand icon, proceed with your bathroom break.

  • Technical Support

    • If you encounter technical problems with Examplify, please notify the proctor following the same procedure for seeking clarifications on test questions.

    • Note that there will be no technical support for PostgreSQL during the test.

  • Important: Periodically check that your Zoom camera is active and connected. If you have been disconnected, please reconnect immediately.

  • The proctor may unmute/mute your microphone as required.

5.6. Test Submission

  • The proctor will announce Stop writing when the time is up.

  • If you’d joined the Zoom meeting early before the test password was announced, your Examplify timer will have timed out or will be timed out soon. You may submit your test paper following these instructions.

  • However, if you’d joined the Zoom meeting late after the test password was announced, you must stop your Examplify test and submit the test paper immediately (even if your Examplify timer has not counted down to zero) following these instructions.

    • Late comers who continue to work on the test paper after the stop writing announcement will be reported for disciplinary action.

  • After you’ve submitted your test paper, turn on Zoom’s "Yes" green check mark as follows:

    • Tap on the phone to show a menu at the bottom of the Zoom app.

    • Tap on the More button ("…​") at the right corner of the menu to show a submenu and click on the Check mark button.

  • You are not allowed to leave the Zoom meeting after your submission. You must remain in the Zoom meeting until the proctor has announced that you may leave the meeting.

5.7. End of Test

  • You may leave the Zoom meeting after the proctor has announced End of test.

  • Stop the PC screen recording & upload the recording to LumiNUS following steps 12 to 15 in Using Panopto.

6. Installing & Using Panopto

You will use CIT’s web-based Panopto to record your PC screen.

For technical help with Panopto, please visit https://cithelp.nus.edu.sg/servicedesk/customer/portal/4/group/24.

6.1. Installing Panopto

  1. In LumiNUS, click CS2102 under My Modules > Enrolled Modules.

  2. Scroll down on the left-hand sidebar. Click Multimedia.

  3. Click on channel CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording.

  4. Within the channel, click on the folder named CS2102 - [2120] 2021/2022 Semester 2: CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording [assignments]

  5. Click on the Create button at the top of your page. Select Panopto for Windows or Panopto for Mac. The following popup window will appear.

  6. In the popup window, click on the Download Panopto button. Wait for the installer to be downloaded.

  7. Install Panopto. If you encounter any issues during installation, disable any anti-virus software and firewall, and try again.

  8. Panopto will be launched after the installation is complete.

6.2. Using Panopto

  1. In LumiNUS, click CS2102 under My Modules > Enrolled Modules.

  2. Scroll down on the left-hand sidebar. Click Multimedia.

  3. Click on channel CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording.

  4. Within the channel, click on the folder named CS2102 - [2120] 2021/2022 Semester 2: CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording [assignments]

  5. Click on the Create button at the top of your page. Select Panopto for Windows or Panopto for Mac. A popup window appears.

  6. In the popup window, click on the Open Panopto button. Panopto will be launched.

  7. Verify in the main window of Panopto that

    1. You are logged in to Panopto.

    2. The Folder is correctly pointing to CS2102 - [2120] 2021/2022 Semester 2: CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording [assignments]

  8. For Windows users, configure Panopto Settings as follows:

    1. Click Settings on the top of the Panopto window.

    2. Under Basic Settings, uncheck Progressively upload while recording.

    3. Under Advanced Settings, uncheck Enable no audio detected alerts.

    4. Under Advanced Settings, check Capture in MP4 format.

    5. Click Save at the bottom of the window. You should have returned to the default page Create New Recording.

  9. For Mac Users, you need not make any changes to the settings.

  10. Configure new recording setups on Create New Recording page:

    1. Under Session Settings, set Name of your recording as "XX_Mock Exam", where XX is your NUS userid; e.g., "E0123456_Mock Exam".

    2. On the left panel of the window, under Primary Sources,

      1. Select Video sources to be None.

      2. Check Capture Computer Audio.

    3. On the left panel of the window, under Secondary Sources,

      1. Uncheck Capture PowerPoint.

    4. On the bottom of the right panel Main Screen (NOTE: this step can be omitted if the panel is missing on your screen),

      1. Set fps to be the minimum allowed (4).

      2. Set kbps to be the minimum allowed (340).

  11. Start recording by clicking on the Record button on top left of the Create New Recording window. Note that you have to select an audio source in order to enable the Record button, if your computer does not have an audio device, please notify the proctor following the same procedure for seeking clarifications on test questions.

  12. When the proctor announces the end of the mock exam, click Stop on top left of the Create New Recording window. A popup will appear indicating Recording is Complete.

  13. Click Done on the popup.

  14. Your recording is currently being uploaded to the folder CS2102 - [2120] 2021/2022 Semester 2: CS2102 Mock Exam Screen Recording [assignments]. You should see the status of your recording similar to the screenshot below after the recording is uploaded successfully.

  15. Check the Luminus folder that your recording is now displayed in the Luminus folder.

  16. Congratulations, you have successfully uploaded your screen recording.
